[Malaria is endemic throughout Angola, with an estimated incidence of 120 cases per 1000 population per year (WHO World Malaria Report 2016). All cases are caused by _Plasmodium falciparum_. The malaria burden has gradually increased from an estimated 50 cases per 1000 population in 2005 (http://www.who.int/malaria/publications/world-malaria-report-2016/WMR-2016-profiles.pdf). However, reported cases underestimate the real number. The national malaria control program is funded almost entirely by external donors. - Mod.EP

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5008632,165.]
